</ul>
<p><strong>Total: $30-35 billion annually from immediate reforms,
scaling to $150-200 billion as enforcement improves</strong></p>
<p>This isn’t about punishing success—it’s about ensuring everyone
contributes their fair share to the society that enabled their
prosperity. Warren Buffett has repeatedly noted the absurdity of paying
a lower effective tax rate than his secretary. Closing these loopholes
would simply ensure the tax code operates as intended.</p>
