<p><strong>3. Increased production capacity</strong> - Automation
increases supply of goods/services - Inflation requires demand exceeding
supply - But supply is increasing faster than demand</p>
<p><strong>4. Historical evidence</strong> - Alaska: 40 years of annual
payments, no inflation - COVID stimulus: Inflation was supply-chain, not
cash-driven - UBI trials: No inflationary effects observed</p>
