<p>For millennia, human civilization has been constrained by scarcity.
Economic systems evolved to manage scarcity: to determine who gets what
limited resources exist.</p>
<p>But the 21st century is different. For the first time in history,
technology makes material abundance possible: - <strong>Energy
abundance</strong> through fusion - <strong>Manufacturing
abundance</strong> through robotics - <strong>Information
abundance</strong> through AI</p>
<p>The question is no longer “how do we divide scarcity?” but “how do we
share abundance?”</p>
<p>Universal Basic Income is not just an economic policy—it’s the social
contract for the age of abundance.</p>
